		<info>
			<li><b>Biotic Stress - <i>Golovinomyces orontii</i></b>; data provided by the Wildermuth Lab (Chandran et al., 2010. PNAS 107(1).) </li>
			<li>Plant material from uninfected and <i>G. orontii</i> infected 4 week old wild-type and <i>ics1-2</i> mutant (<i>eds16</i>) <i>Arabidopsis thaliana</i> plants of Columbia-0 ecotype were analyzed</li>
			<li>Parallel experiments were also carried out using while leaves and leaf scrape for some of the samples</li>
			<li>Plants grown in evenly spaced boxes were infected with <i>G. orontii</i> using a settling tower and mesh screen</li>
			<li>Plants were grown under 12/12 hour light/dark conditions</li>
			<li>Groups of epidermal and mesophyll cells surrounding the infected cells were collected using Leica AS LMD with 40XT objective</li>
			<li>Two of the six biological replicates were processed - the average of which is shown</li>
			<li>RNA was isolated and hybridized to the ATH1 GeneChip</li>
			<li>The data were normalized by GCOS normalization, TGT 100</li>
		</info>
